President Trump holds a ceremony in the Oval Office to swear in Mark T. Esper as the new Secretary of Defense. Trump thanks the Republican senators for their support and mentions that the Senate vote was 90 to 8 in favor of Esper's appointment. He praises Esper's qualifications and his previous role as Secretary of the Army. Esper is a West Point graduate and has served in the military for 21 years. He holds a doctorate in public policy and a master's degree in public administration. Esper expresses gratitude for the appointment and promises to lead the military with energy and commitment. He also mentions the importance of taking care of military families. Trump presents Esper with a certificate and congratulates him on his new position.